		<text>f the script also contains the doubleBeep handler (or if the script of any object later in the message-passing path contains it), the mouseUp message will send the doubleBeep message, and doubleBeep will send two beep commands. Because beep is a built-in command, HyperCard beeps twice.If HyperCard can’t find the doubleBeep message, it will complain (with a dialog box) that it “can’t understand” the message.</text>
